WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.000 --> 00:00:03.696
I need to talk to you. If it's
about Vadim. I will talk to MI6.

2
00:00:03.720 --> 00:00:05.376
but right now. I'm in the middle...
It's not about Vadim.

3
00:00:05.400 --> 00:00:07.136
It's something else.
Saara has something for us. Charlie.

4
00:00:07.160 --> 00:00:08.856
It's how the Russian malware
got into our system.

5
00:00:08.880 --> 00:00:10.496
Writers of the code had to have it

6
00:00:10.520 --> 00:00:12.176
before it ever arrived at GCHQ.

7
00:00:12.200 --> 00:00:13.896
In old money. a mole.

8
00:00:13.920 --> 00:00:15.216
One of us.

9
00:00:15.240 --> 00:00:18.416
Mr Makinde has seen fit
to appoint me Foreign Secretary.

10
00:00:18.440 --> 00:00:21.056
I am seconding a team from
the Fourteenth Signal Regiment

11
00:00:21.080 --> 00:00:24.896
and appointing their CO to the new
post of Director of Rapid Reaction.

12
00:00:24.920 --> 00:00:26.736
So they probably think you're
the firing squad come for me.

13
00:00:26.760 --> 00:00:27.936
Maybe we are.

14
00:00:27.960 --> 00:00:29.856
Don't you ever dream of just
jacking it all in?

15
00:00:29.880 --> 00:00:31.936
Dream. perhaps.
but if everyone thought like that...

16
00:00:31.960 --> 00:00:34.376
There'd be no-one left
to save the world.

17
00:00:34.400 --> 00:00:37.336
Secret report on CCP activities in
managed asset pools.

18
00:00:37.360 --> 00:00:38.776
Let's give it our best shot. team.

19
00:00:38.800 --> 00:00:40.536
Alex.
They've had a sighting of Trusov.

20
00:00:40.560 --> 00:00:43.416
If the FSB have got him.
it can only be a matter of time.

21
00:00:43.440 --> 00:00:45.896
The news on Vadim is
not so good. I'm afraid.

22
00:00:45.920 --> 00:00:47.240
What will they be doing to him?

23
00:00:51.920 --> 00:00:54.920
This programme contains strong
language.

24
00:01:50.880 --> 00:01:51.896
Sit.

25
00:01:51.920 --> 00:01:53.616
Glass of wine.

26
00:01:53.640 --> 00:01:55.056
Dinner.

27
00:01:55.080 --> 00:01:56.736
Special occasion?

28
00:01:56.760 --> 00:01:59.560
You're home. I'm home -
that's rare enough these days.

29
00:02:01.840 --> 00:02:03.896
You didn't! Taj Mahal.

30
00:02:03.920 --> 00:02:05.856
I was just passing and...

31
00:02:05.880 --> 00:02:08.336
"Chicken tikka masala for sir."
BARBARA LAUGHS.

32
00:02:08.360 --> 00:02:10.256
"Jalfrezi for the lady."

33
00:02:10.280 --> 00:02:13.480
PHONE RINGS Aw...

34
00:02:18.240 --> 00:02:19.840
Sorry. Go on.

35
00:02:22.720 --> 00:02:24.576
Yes. Danny Patrick?

36
00:02:24.600 --> 00:02:25.896
Yes?

37
00:02:25.920 --> 00:02:27.896
Maya Young. Deputy Head of Security.

38
00:02:27.920 --> 00:02:29.576
We're on a secure line.

39
00:02:29.600 --> 00:02:30.776
What's up?

40
00:02:30.800 --> 00:02:32.736
I have Saara Parvin here.

41
00:02:32.760 --> 00:02:34.776
She's been communicating with
a third party

42
00:02:34.800 --> 00:02:37.416
through a Discord server
from the event management centre.

43
00:02:37.440 --> 00:02:38.896
She says you'll vouch for her.

44
00:02:38.920 --> 00:02:40.320
Let me speak to her.

45
00:02:43.560 --> 00:02:44.816
It's me. Danny.

46
00:02:44.840 --> 00:02:46.016
What's going on. Saara?

47
00:02:46.040 --> 00:02:47.416
It's Vadim - he's alive.

48
00:02:47.440 --> 00:02:50.136
Oh. that's great news.
How is he? Where is he?

49
00:02:50.160 --> 00:02:51.936
That's the thing -
he says it wasn't Russia.

50
00:02:51.960 --> 00:02:54.056
the attack. Stage 3.
the data scrape -

51
00:02:54.080 --> 00:02:56.016
or it was them
but it wasn't for them.

52
00:02:56.040 --> 00:02:59.256
Sorry. what wasn't? Who was it for?

53
00:02:59.280 --> 00:03:02.360
Stage 3 was China. Vadim's in China.

54
00:03:04.920 --> 00:03:06.360
Everything OK?

55
00:03:59.080 --> 00:04:01.616
NEWSREADER: The growing military
relationship between

56
00:04:01.640 --> 00:04:04.256
China and Russia
is a major concern for the West.

57
00:04:04.280 --> 00:04:07.496
Trade between the two countries is
at an all-time high.

58
00:04:07.520 --> 00:04:10.416
Hostile nation states are waging
a new kind of war.

59
00:04:10.440 --> 00:04:14.016
launching cyber-attacks that are
capable of crippling infrastructure.

60
00:04:14.040 --> 00:04:15.136
causing chaos.

61
00:04:15.160 --> 00:04:18.920
Presidents Xi and Putin have called
for a new global order.

62
00:04:32.040 --> 00:04:33.496
Welcome. Russian coders.

63
00:04:33.520 --> 00:04:35.616
Welcome to China.
welcome to Shenzhen.

64
00:04:35.640 --> 00:04:37.016
As part of the no-limits partnership

65
00:04:37.040 --> 00:04:40.136
as agreed by our gracious
Presidents Xi and Putin.

66
00:04:40.160 --> 00:04:42.040
you are our honoured guests.

67
00:04:48.120 --> 00:04:50.120
DOOR SLIDES OPENS

68
00:04:51.640 --> 00:04:54.616
I am Ming Liu. your translator.
You'll call me Liu.

69
00:04:54.640 --> 00:04:57.496
We speak English not because
English is a superior language

70
00:04:57.520 --> 00:05:00.560
but because English is the
international language of coding.

71
00:05:07.120 --> 00:05:08.496
Yin Technologies.

72
00:05:08.520 --> 00:05:10.216
We are proud to be recognised
in the West

73
00:05:10.240 --> 00:05:12.096
as one of the most sophisticated.

74
00:05:12.120 --> 00:05:14.856
significant and sustained
cyber attackers in the world.

75
00:05:14.880 --> 00:05:17.576
IN RUSSIAN:

76
00:05:17.600 --> 00:05:21.776
Yin Technologies is an independent.
cyber-development enterprise.

77
00:05:21.800 --> 00:05:24.640
We work from eight to six.
lunch at midday.

78
00:05:28.880 --> 00:05:30.816
You can of course work more
if you so wish.

79
00:05:30.840 --> 00:05:32.720
the job will be done quicker.

80
00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:41.776
English. please.

81
00:05:41.800 --> 00:05:43.936
Ming Liu.

82
00:05:43.960 --> 00:05:47.176
I have three children.
and my wife works.

83
00:05:47.200 --> 00:05:50.696
No-one knows that I'm here.
nor anyone's family.

84
00:05:50.720 --> 00:05:53.856
We had to hand over all phones
and all personal devices.

85
00:05:53.880 --> 00:05:55.336
I'm sure your families
will be informed

86
00:05:55.360 --> 00:05:57.880
that you are engaged in
important work for your nation.

87
00:06:03.000 --> 00:06:04.976
This is the breaking and
entering tool we built

88
00:06:05.000 --> 00:06:06.736
for the attack on the UK.

89
00:06:06.760 --> 00:06:09.496
As you are aware. in your recent
exploit against the United Kingdom.

90
00:06:09.520 --> 00:06:11.096
there were three stages
to your attack.

91
00:06:11.120 --> 00:06:14.960
and you are here to redesign your
breaking and entering tool for us.

92
00:06:17.240 --> 00:06:18.816
To break in where?

93
00:06:18.840 --> 00:06:21.240
You only need to know what is
essential to your job.

94
00:06:22.720 --> 00:06:24.816
I will assign tasks
tomorrow morning.

95
00:06:24.840 --> 00:06:26.160
Now. you sleep.

96
00:06:29.360 --> 00:06:30.976
We sleep here too?

97
00:06:31.000 --> 00:06:33.200
Yes. for your comfort.

98
00:06:34.800 --> 00:06:36.216
We have all the latest games...

99
00:06:36.240 --> 00:06:38.816
MISHA SIGHS
we will call out for food.

100
00:06:38.840 --> 00:06:41.216
Otherwise. you have everything
you need here -

101
00:06:41.240 --> 00:06:44.680
clothing. bedding. toiletries.
your welcome pack.

102
00:06:47.000 --> 00:06:48.240
So we are prisoners?

103
00:06:51.280 --> 00:06:52.880
You are our honoured guests.

104
00:07:55.440 --> 00:07:57.896
VADIM SIGHS

105
00:07:57.920 --> 00:08:00.680
VIDEO GAMES SOUND EFFECTS

106
00:08:44.720 --> 00:08:47.136
Please check the menu for your food.

107
00:08:47.160 --> 00:08:48.640
I will take your order after.

108
00:09:04.440 --> 00:09:06.640
TEXT ALERT

109
00:11:10.840 --> 00:11:12.400
{\an8}I'm really glad it's you. Saara.

110
00:12:14.040 --> 00:12:16.080
COMPUTER BEEPS

111
00:12:49.120 --> 00:12:52.896
No-one else would use your login
on the sandbox. right?

112
00:12:52.920 --> 00:12:53.920
No.

113
00:12:55.040 --> 00:12:57.976
And you'd never leave it unattended
while you were logged on?

114
00:12:58.000 --> 00:12:59.400
Never. Hm.

115
00:13:01.840 --> 00:13:04.536
What about people working with you

116
00:13:04.560 --> 00:13:06.136
while you're logged on?

117
00:13:06.160 --> 00:13:09.296
Sure. but I'm always there.

118
00:13:09.320 --> 00:13:12.696
Do you remember working
with any Russian specialists

119
00:13:12.720 --> 00:13:15.800
between these dates in 2022?

120
00:13:20.320 --> 00:13:23.176
What. a three-month period
two years ago?

121
00:13:23.200 --> 00:13:24.856
I mean. during a surge.

122
00:13:24.880 --> 00:13:28.336
I could log on to the sandbox
seven times a day.

123
00:13:28.360 --> 00:13:30.600
so. yeah. it's possible.

124
00:13:36.920 --> 00:13:38.176
But none in particular?

125
00:13:38.200 --> 00:13:41.680
Well. I'd need a particular time
to be particular.

126
00:13:43.920 --> 00:13:45.456
Even then. it's...

127
00:13:45.480 --> 00:13:47.376
Sorry. what's this about?

128
00:13:47.400 --> 00:13:50.296
I need to review your
security status.

129
00:13:50.320 --> 00:13:51.616
Sure. but...

130
00:13:51.640 --> 00:13:54.776
Any changes in your circumstances
since your last review?

131
00:13:54.800 --> 00:13:57.096
How do you mean? Financial? Lovers?

132
00:13:57.120 --> 00:13:58.856
Old friends who have
come back into your life?

133
00:13:58.880 --> 00:14:00.360
New friends?

134
00:14:03.880 --> 00:14:04.880
Yeah. Yes.

135
00:14:06.280 --> 00:14:08.776
There is actually something I...
PHIL CLEARS THROAT

136
00:14:08.800 --> 00:14:10.360
I should declare.

137
00:14:13.120 --> 00:14:15.896
We only have Trusov's word for it
that the Chinese are involved.

138
00:14:15.920 --> 00:14:17.656
that he's even in China.

139
00:14:17.680 --> 00:14:21.376
We've ignored Vadim before.
to our cost.

140
00:14:21.400 --> 00:14:22.976
How can she be sure it was him?

141
00:14:23.000 --> 00:14:25.416
I told you. she asked him
something only he would know.

142
00:14:25.440 --> 00:14:28.056
OK. so it's him.
Maybe they have him under duress.

143
00:14:28.080 --> 00:14:29.776
or maybe they've been playing
the long game with him.

144
00:14:29.800 --> 00:14:31.120
and us. all along.

145
00:14:32.440 --> 00:14:33.640
Fair conjecture. Danny.

146
00:14:35.720 --> 00:14:37.496
All right. I accept that
that's a possibility.

147
00:14:37.520 --> 00:14:40.376
Which means we should treat
the intel with the utmost caution.

148
00:14:40.400 --> 00:14:43.576
I accept that it's a possibility
but I don't buy it.

149
00:14:43.600 --> 00:14:46.576
The FSB data Vadim leaked us.
you've seen it -

150
00:14:46.600 --> 00:14:48.256
there's no way that was a play.

151
00:14:48.280 --> 00:14:50.136
He even gave us
a back door into their system.

152
00:14:50.160 --> 00:14:51.736
So. yes. I trust the source.

153
00:14:51.760 --> 00:14:53.240
What evidence have we in the code?

154
00:14:55.040 --> 00:14:56.400
It was a fair question. Danny.

155
00:14:57.520 --> 00:15:00.456
We haven't seen any evidence
of Chinese involvement in the code

156
00:15:00.480 --> 00:15:02.416
because we weren't looking at them.

157
00:15:02.440 --> 00:15:05.216
All right. if you've both had
your say. moving forward.

158
00:15:05.240 --> 00:15:07.696
what do we know about offensive
cyber operations in Shenzhen?

159
00:15:07.720 --> 00:15:10.896
APT10. one of the largest and
longest-established...

160
00:15:10.920 --> 00:15:13.256
It's an arm's length MSS operation -

161
00:15:13.280 --> 00:15:15.016
Chinese Ministry of State Security -

162
00:15:15.040 --> 00:15:17.696
and we would be unwise
to ignore the intel.

163
00:15:17.720 --> 00:15:20.336
If Russia and China
are collaborating on cyber.

164
00:15:20.360 --> 00:15:22.856
it represents a major threat
to national security.

165
00:15:22.880 --> 00:15:24.576
Danny and I will have
to travel to London

166
00:15:24.600 --> 00:15:26.416
to brief the Foreign Secretary.

167
00:15:26.440 --> 00:15:28.296
We'll need to check through
the malware code.

168
00:15:28.320 --> 00:15:30.960
Would you please see to this
personally. Lieutenant Colonel?

169
00:15:32.480 --> 00:15:35.096
Sir. with due respect.

170
00:15:35.120 --> 00:15:38.096
I'm Director of Rapid Reaction.
not a reverse engineer.

171
00:15:38.120 --> 00:15:41.816
Until such time as we can offer
better proof of attribution.

172
00:15:41.840 --> 00:15:44.256
China's possible involvement
must stay between us.

173
00:15:44.280 --> 00:15:48.336
Still. sir... For this.
and other reasons I can't go into.

174
00:15:48.360 --> 00:15:50.880
I kindly request that you look into
this yourself.

175
00:15:53.120 --> 00:15:54.120
Yes. sir.

176
00:15:57.520 --> 00:16:01.056
You might want to check and see if
we've seen any of the code before.

177
00:16:01.080 --> 00:16:03.680
anything to link
the data scrape back to the CCP.

178
00:16:06.520 --> 00:16:08.816
One more thing. both of you.

179
00:16:08.840 --> 00:16:10.976
This. all of this. is more important.

180
00:16:11.000 --> 00:16:14.160
much more important.
than your two bruised egos.

181
00:16:22.600 --> 00:16:24.040
CHARLIE: Wow.

182
00:16:25.280 --> 00:16:28.656
And your friend Jules.
he bankrolled it?

183
00:16:28.680 --> 00:16:30.200
Yeah. his start-up did. yeah.

184
00:16:32.760 --> 00:16:33.840
How?

185
00:16:35.440 --> 00:16:37.536
Venture capital? I don't know.

186
00:16:37.560 --> 00:16:40.416
My job was to design the game.

187
00:16:40.440 --> 00:16:42.736
Destiny Doom Loop?

188
00:16:42.760 --> 00:16:43.960
I write code. OK? I don't...

189
00:16:45.440 --> 00:16:47.736
come up with the names
or do the deals.

190
00:16:47.760 --> 00:16:49.336
Did Jules approach you. or you him?

191
00:16:49.360 --> 00:16:51.016
I think he came to me. It's...

192
00:16:51.040 --> 00:16:52.176
Is that important?

193
00:16:52.200 --> 00:16:54.576
And there were no
Russian connections.

194
00:16:54.600 --> 00:16:56.416
his gaming company.

195
00:16:56.440 --> 00:16:57.736
that you're aware of?

196
00:16:57.760 --> 00:16:59.936
It's a dystopian. shoot-em-up game -

197
00:16:59.960 --> 00:17:03.496
it's hardly divulging
strap three intel.

198
00:17:03.520 --> 00:17:06.576
And it's not against the rules
to do a bit of moonlighting. OK?

199
00:17:06.600 --> 00:17:08.096
Me and the other programmers.

200
00:17:08.120 --> 00:17:11.920
we could earn ten times what we're
earning here in the private sector.

201
00:17:19.040 --> 00:17:20.040
Right.

202
00:17:34.080 --> 00:17:35.080
Phil.

203
00:17:37.200 --> 00:17:39.656
Have a look at investors
going back three years

204
00:17:39.680 --> 00:17:41.576
and check his personal accounts -

205
00:17:41.600 --> 00:17:42.920
high street. crypto...

206
00:17:44.280 --> 00:17:45.456
et cetera.

207
00:17:45.480 --> 00:17:47.656
Any big deposits.

208
00:17:47.680 --> 00:17:49.096
KNOCKING

209
00:17:49.120 --> 00:17:50.496
Sorry to interrupt.

210
00:17:50.520 --> 00:17:51.856
You remember my deputy?

211
00:17:51.880 --> 00:17:52.936
Maya Young.

212
00:17:52.960 --> 00:17:54.160
Yes. we spoke on the phone.

213
00:17:55.640 --> 00:17:56.760
Boss.

214
00:18:00.520 --> 00:18:02.576
Any progress on our mole?

215
00:18:02.600 --> 00:18:04.616
Sifting through the hay
piece by piece.

216
00:18:04.640 --> 00:18:08.656
Well. I don't want to make that
stack any bigger but...

217
00:18:08.680 --> 00:18:10.056
What?

218
00:18:10.080 --> 00:18:12.376
That Russian connection you're
looking for...

219
00:18:12.400 --> 00:18:13.896
Yes?

220
00:18:13.920 --> 00:18:15.400
It might not. in fact. be Russian.

221
00:18:17.720 --> 00:18:19.056
Yeah. it reads well.

222
00:18:19.080 --> 00:18:20.296
Very well.

223
00:18:20.320 --> 00:18:21.696
The ending. Calvin.

224
00:18:21.720 --> 00:18:23.656
fair reflection of the original?

225
00:18:23.680 --> 00:18:25.416
Yes. Barbara. I think so.

226
00:18:25.440 --> 00:18:27.720
That's good.
Good report. Lydia. Well done.

227
00:18:28.840 --> 00:18:31.096
Oh. hello. Hello.

228
00:18:31.120 --> 00:18:33.056
Well. if it's a lunch date
you were hoping for.

229
00:18:33.080 --> 00:18:34.520
I'm afraid today is team lunch.

230
00:18:35.960 --> 00:18:39.976
Hey. is there somewhere we can talk
a bit more privately?

231
00:18:40.000 --> 00:18:41.616
What is it? The boys?

232
00:18:41.640 --> 00:18:43.616
No. no. no. no. Just...

233
00:18:43.640 --> 00:18:45.240
Yeah. sure.

234
00:19:00.440 --> 00:19:02.056
So...?

235
00:19:02.080 --> 00:19:03.856
I was wondering.

236
00:19:03.880 --> 00:19:08.896
anything new or unusual coming
through reports?

237
00:19:08.920 --> 00:19:10.080
From China?

238
00:19:11.320 --> 00:19:13.016
Well. all the time.

239
00:19:13.040 --> 00:19:15.856
but if there was anything
relating to you.

240
00:19:15.880 --> 00:19:17.080
it would have been passed on.

241
00:19:18.400 --> 00:19:20.960
Can you be more explicit?
Mm. afraid not.

242
00:19:23.680 --> 00:19:24.896
You come to me wanting answers

243
00:19:24.920 --> 00:19:26.600
and I've got to
come up with the questions?

244
00:19:27.880 --> 00:19:30.216
No. no. Not that I'm aware of.

245
00:19:30.240 --> 00:19:36.176
Look. if they were after something
in here. then what might that be?

246
00:19:36.200 --> 00:19:38.376
They're in here?
Not that we know of.

247
00:19:38.400 --> 00:19:41.400
but if they were. what do you think
they'd be looking for?

248
00:19:42.760 --> 00:19:45.936
Well. I suppose speculation
doesn't count as disclosure.

249
00:19:45.960 --> 00:19:47.080
I believe not.

250
00:19:49.720 --> 00:19:50.896
Everything.

251
00:19:50.920 --> 00:19:52.080
I mean. they love data.

252
00:19:53.200 --> 00:19:55.976
And. of course. anything
in relation to Hong Kong.

253
00:19:56.000 --> 00:19:57.936
Tibet. Uighurs. Taiwan.

254
00:19:57.960 --> 00:20:00.176
but they're quiet on all that
at present.

255
00:20:00.200 --> 00:20:03.520
The main thing in relation to us
is the trade deal.

256
00:20:05.200 --> 00:20:08.856
But the Department of Trade and
Industry or the Treasury.

257
00:20:08.880 --> 00:20:12.576
they hold our significant
economic data. not us.

258
00:20:12.600 --> 00:20:14.440
There's much richer pickings there.

259
00:20:15.960 --> 00:20:20.296
We're just security profiling
their industries and state bodies.

260
00:20:20.320 --> 00:20:22.816
Hardly worth the fallout
of an attack

261
00:20:22.840 --> 00:20:24.896
for them finding out
what we know about them.

262
00:20:24.920 --> 00:20:27.336
Now they're attacking us?
I didn't say that.

263
00:20:27.360 --> 00:20:29.200
I said it was hardly worth it.

264
00:20:32.840 --> 00:20:34.176
David's going to be waiting for me.

265
00:20:34.200 --> 00:20:36.296
Oh. well. sorry
I couldn't be of more help.

266
00:20:36.320 --> 00:20:38.416
You've been a lot of help.
Thank you.

267
00:20:38.440 --> 00:20:39.760
Take care.

268
00:20:48.160 --> 00:20:49.800
See you later. OK.

269
00:20:57.040 --> 00:20:59.760
RECORDING OF FEMALE VOICE
SPEAKING MANDARIN

270
00:21:11.720 --> 00:21:14.896
Barbara? Calvin. there's something
I need to attend to.

271
00:21:14.920 --> 00:21:17.696
Kids. Danny's gone to London.

272
00:21:17.720 --> 00:21:18.880
Of course.

273
00:21:26.040 --> 00:21:28.456
PHONE BUZZES

274
00:21:28.480 --> 00:21:29.480
Roz.

275
00:21:30.880 --> 00:21:33.096
We're just coming into London.
what have you found?

276
00:21:33.120 --> 00:21:37.256
I ran the code similarity searches
on our holdings.

277
00:21:37.280 --> 00:21:41.136
The interfaces between stages 2 and
3 have been seen before.

278
00:21:41.160 --> 00:21:43.000
but not in Russian capability.

279
00:21:45.800 --> 00:21:48.216
So the code is Chinese in origin?

280
00:21:48.240 --> 00:21:50.056
Well. yeah. Chinese in origin.

281
00:21:50.080 --> 00:21:54.376
but it does not prove that it is
a Chinese attack.

282
00:21:54.400 --> 00:21:56.176
The Russians could have used it as
part of an attempt

283
00:21:56.200 --> 00:21:57.856
to deflect us towards China.

284
00:21:57.880 --> 00:22:01.096
All right. I'll talk to
MI6 and our Five Eye partners

285
00:22:01.120 --> 00:22:03.656
and see if they have anything to
corroborate or contradict.

286
00:22:03.680 --> 00:22:04.976
In the meantime.

287
00:22:05.000 --> 00:22:07.440
would you write up a report. please?
Thanks.

288
00:22:16.120 --> 00:22:17.816
Alex. short notice.

289
00:22:17.840 --> 00:22:20.736
but we're wondering if you might
have any human intelligence

290
00:22:20.760 --> 00:22:22.960
which speaks to
something we're looking at?

291
00:23:04.560 --> 00:23:06.840
PHONE BUZZES

292
00:23:08.560 --> 00:23:10.360
Marston. Richard...

293
00:23:11.480 --> 00:23:13.056
bit of a heads up.

294
00:23:13.080 --> 00:23:15.136
you're going to be hearing
the recent attack

295
00:23:15.160 --> 00:23:17.480
might not have been
solely the work of the Russians.

296
00:24:10.960 --> 00:24:13.320
PHONE RINGS

297
00:24:19.240 --> 00:24:21.696
Oh. hi. Anne. Um...

298
00:24:21.720 --> 00:24:24.736
Uh... sorry. yeah. too many things.

299
00:24:24.760 --> 00:24:27.016
Look. Dan's been called away again

300
00:24:27.040 --> 00:24:29.176
and we are up to our teeth
in the department -

301
00:24:29.200 --> 00:24:31.456
I don't suppose the boys could come
to yours after school. could they?

302
00:24:31.480 --> 00:24:33.696
Yes. of course. no problem.
No. that's great.

303
00:24:33.720 --> 00:24:35.136
Yeah.
Everything all right with you?

304
00:24:35.160 --> 00:24:36.456
No. no. everything's fine.

305
00:24:36.480 --> 00:24:38.136
Yeah. sure. I'll give them some tea.

306
00:24:38.160 --> 00:24:39.576
Oh. thank you.

307
00:24:39.600 --> 00:24:41.496
All right. No worries. Bye.

308
00:24:41.520 --> 00:24:42.856
OK. yeah. Bye. Barbara.

309
00:24:42.880 --> 00:24:44.240
All right. bye.

310
00:25:32.400 --> 00:25:35.056
{\an8}Vadim Trusov. who we have
good reason to believe

311
00:25:35.080 --> 00:25:37.176
{\an8}alerted us to the involvement
of China state actors

312
00:25:37.200 --> 00:25:39.856
in the recent malware attack APT10.

313
00:25:39.880 --> 00:25:41.936
Lieutenant Colonel Cavendish
confirmed

314
00:25:41.960 --> 00:25:45.616
that the interface for the
Stage 3 malware code originated

315
00:25:45.640 --> 00:25:49.856
in the same Chinese Ministry of
State Security-backed APT10.

316
00:25:49.880 --> 00:25:52.056
There's been an increase in
monitored traffic.

317
00:25:52.080 --> 00:25:55.776
human and electronic. between the
FSB in St Petersburg and Shenzhen -

318
00:25:55.800 --> 00:25:58.016
it would support the theory of
a partnership. Mm.

319
00:25:58.040 --> 00:26:00.456
And despite growing political ties.

320
00:26:00.480 --> 00:26:03.256
a collaboration between Russia
and China on a cyber exploit is.

321
00:26:03.280 --> 00:26:04.896
to date. unheard of.

322
00:26:04.920 --> 00:26:07.616
But you can't be 100% sure.

323
00:26:07.640 --> 00:26:11.856
Well. you can never be 100% sure
when it comes to attribution

324
00:26:11.880 --> 00:26:14.176
unless the one party admits to it.

325
00:26:14.200 --> 00:26:17.096
However. there's a significant
weight of evidence.

326
00:26:17.120 --> 00:26:18.880
We have a high confidence.

327
00:26:21.320 --> 00:26:22.400
Help me out with something.

328
00:26:23.920 --> 00:26:26.496
They're in the middle of
negotiating a huge -

329
00:26:26.520 --> 00:26:27.736
excuse me. David -

330
00:26:27.760 --> 00:26:30.240
a huge trade deal with us.

331
00:26:34.240 --> 00:26:36.456
What exactly would their motive be?

332
00:26:36.480 --> 00:26:40.216
The silent theft of big data
is classic Chinese MO.

333
00:26:40.240 --> 00:26:42.816
So. we can't be 100% sure

334
00:26:42.840 --> 00:26:47.016
and we have no clear motive apart
from their previous charge sheet?

335
00:26:47.040 --> 00:26:50.640
When it was Russia. it demanded
an equal and proportionate response.

336
00:26:52.360 --> 00:26:53.640
MI6's thoughts?

337
00:26:55.000 --> 00:26:56.736
The CCP's quest for big data

338
00:26:56.760 --> 00:27:00.656
has been historically to tighten
control of their own population

339
00:27:00.680 --> 00:27:02.736
or for industrial espionage.

340
00:27:02.760 --> 00:27:05.280
In short.
for their own internal purposes.

341
00:27:07.240 --> 00:27:10.816
China already wields power over our
key technologies.

342
00:27:10.840 --> 00:27:13.816
utilities. internet.
social networks.

343
00:27:13.840 --> 00:27:16.416
They have directly or indirectly
bought the influence of...

344
00:27:16.440 --> 00:27:21.336
Nonetheless. we can only advise
government of the potential threats.

345
00:27:21.360 --> 00:27:23.600
Thank you. Director GCHQ.

346
00:27:26.240 --> 00:27:30.216
Sometimes. we must put
our economic interests before...

347
00:27:30.240 --> 00:27:31.320
Our principles?

348
00:27:36.040 --> 00:27:37.496
Before suspected threats.

349
00:27:37.520 --> 00:27:39.816
the aims of which are. at best.

350
00:27:39.840 --> 00:27:41.000
unclear.

351
00:27:50.440 --> 00:27:52.520
Danny. a word?

352
00:28:00.040 --> 00:28:03.896
So. reports of Mr Trusov's demise
were greatly exaggerated?

353
00:28:03.920 --> 00:28:07.016
Yeah. Do you think you can get him
out of China?

354
00:28:07.040 --> 00:28:09.616
It's possible. but complicated.

355
00:28:09.640 --> 00:28:12.456
and there seems a reluctance
to ruffle CCP feathers.

356
00:28:12.480 --> 00:28:14.296
Yeah. I can see that.

357
00:28:14.320 --> 00:28:16.360
I suppose ruffling
would be inevitable.

358
00:28:17.480 --> 00:28:19.856
And a special op would need not only
Marston's sign-off

359
00:28:19.880 --> 00:28:21.080
but also the PM's.

360
00:28:23.040 --> 00:28:25.376
If you can get your Vadim Trusov
to find out

361
00:28:25.400 --> 00:28:27.856
what the CCP were looking for
in our data.

362
00:28:27.880 --> 00:28:29.456
then not only would our masters

363
00:28:29.480 --> 00:28:33.416
be bound to sanction the
exfiltration.

364
00:28:33.440 --> 00:28:36.960
but also to respond to China's
involvement in the attack.

365
00:28:39.120 --> 00:28:42.296
OK.
And a word to the wise. Danny -

366
00:28:42.320 --> 00:28:45.216
sometimes - well. most times -

367
00:28:45.240 --> 00:28:47.696
it's not about managing the enemy.

368
00:28:47.720 --> 00:28:49.080
it's about managing them.

369
00:28:51.720 --> 00:28:53.520
See you. Danny. Alex.

370
00:28:55.000 --> 00:28:57.520
Oh. and. Danny?

371
00:28:59.000 --> 00:29:00.200
Love to Barbara.

372
00:29:02.520 --> 00:29:05.216
DOOR SHUTS Hello?

373
00:29:05.240 --> 00:29:07.480
Saara. can you get a message
to Vadim?

374
00:29:26.840 --> 00:29:29.160
RUSSIAN CHATTER

375
00:30:06.880 --> 00:30:08.216
Hey. Liu.

376
00:30:08.240 --> 00:30:10.816
I'm done here with recoding
the search tool.

377
00:30:10.840 --> 00:30:11.840
Have you run it?

378
00:30:12.920 --> 00:30:15.136
No. because it needs to know
what it's searching for.

379
00:30:15.160 --> 00:30:17.816
I will run it. Please stand away
from your terminal.

380
00:30:17.840 --> 00:30:20.000
OK. just let me close a few windows.

381
00:30:57.760 --> 00:30:58.760
It's good.

382
00:31:02.960 --> 00:31:04.216
It's time to eat.

383
00:31:04.240 --> 00:31:05.400
I will print out the menus.

384
00:31:20.480 --> 00:31:22.640
DOOR SHUTS

385
00:31:59.840 --> 00:32:00.840
Lunch.

386
00:32:28.800 --> 00:32:31.016
NEWSREADER: Prime Minister
Andrew Makinde continues

387
00:32:31.040 --> 00:32:32.576
his landmark trade talks with China.

388
00:32:32.600 --> 00:32:35.736
Critics say the Government is naive
to hand China access.

389
00:32:35.760 --> 00:32:38.136
Makinde should put down his
begging bowl and

390
00:32:38.160 --> 00:32:40.240
consider British national security.

391
00:32:54.280 --> 00:32:56.056
You've been on that since dinner -
what is it?

392
00:32:56.080 --> 00:32:57.400
Ay-ay-ay-ay.

393
00:32:58.880 --> 00:33:00.936
It's in the public realm.
I suppose.

394
00:33:00.960 --> 00:33:04.216
Marston allegedly taking bribes
for the nuclear deal?

395
00:33:04.240 --> 00:33:05.240
China again?

396
00:33:06.400 --> 00:33:08.480
Your team worked on the inquiry.
didn't they?

397
00:33:10.160 --> 00:33:11.520
I couldn't possibly comment.

398
00:33:13.360 --> 00:33:14.760
I get it - payback.

399
00:33:16.760 --> 00:33:18.816
We made submissions -
what they were. I can't tell you.

400
00:33:18.840 --> 00:33:20.216
Why do you want to know?

401
00:33:20.240 --> 00:33:22.160
Do you think the inquiry was
a whitewash?

402
00:33:24.000 --> 00:33:25.320
Come on. aren't they always?

403
00:33:27.200 --> 00:33:29.496
You know what? I don't like Marston

404
00:33:29.520 --> 00:33:33.736
and his "Rule Britannia"
Empire politics but.

405
00:33:33.760 --> 00:33:35.400
well. they couldn't find
anything on him.

406
00:33:44.880 --> 00:33:46.280
Hey.

407
00:33:54.160 --> 00:33:55.480
Come here.

408
00:34:07.640 --> 00:34:09.200
Morning. Charlotte. Morning.

409
00:34:18.520 --> 00:34:20.256
Thanks for your help yesterday.

410
00:34:20.280 --> 00:34:21.496
It's OK.

411
00:34:21.520 --> 00:34:22.816
I enjoyed it.

412
00:34:22.840 --> 00:34:24.496
A little bit. anyway.

413
00:34:24.520 --> 00:34:25.976
What did they say?

414
00:34:26.000 --> 00:34:28.056
Well. the Foreign Secretary didn't
seem too surprised

415
00:34:28.080 --> 00:34:29.760
at the mention of
Chinese involvement.

416
00:34:31.160 --> 00:34:33.376
I meant what I said about
going behind people's backs.

417
00:34:33.400 --> 00:34:36.056
Who went behind
the Foreign Secretary to the NSA?

418
00:34:36.080 --> 00:34:37.336
You're right.

419
00:34:37.360 --> 00:34:40.296
but I've realised it wasn't
the best move.

420
00:34:40.320 --> 00:34:42.176
"Win a battle. lose the war."
and all that.

421
00:34:42.200 --> 00:34:44.400
You don't need to use military
metaphors for my benefit.

422
00:34:45.400 --> 00:34:49.376
All right. There's no harm in the
Foreign Secretary being pre-briefed.

423
00:34:49.400 --> 00:34:51.816
It allows him to
consider a response.

424
00:34:51.840 --> 00:34:53.536
I got a response. all right.

425
00:34:53.560 --> 00:34:56.136
For someone so intent on action.
he seems strangely reluctant

426
00:34:56.160 --> 00:34:58.240
to consider even
the smallest complaint to China.

427
00:34:59.320 --> 00:35:01.280
I presume he'll downplay it to
the Prime Minister.

428
00:35:03.240 --> 00:35:04.520
Well. what do you suggest we do?

429
00:35:07.160 --> 00:35:10.576
Well. we keep a skeleton team
on the FSB

430
00:35:10.600 --> 00:35:13.496
and your team tries
to understand what China were after.

431
00:35:13.520 --> 00:35:14.736
If we know that.

432
00:35:14.760 --> 00:35:17.000
then the case for a considered
response will be stronger.

433
00:35:18.880 --> 00:35:20.200
OK.

434
00:35:26.480 --> 00:35:28.816
Good morning. team.
ALL: Morning. sir.

435
00:35:28.840 --> 00:35:31.440
RECORDING OF FEMALE VOICE
SPEAKING MANDARIN

436
00:35:38.920 --> 00:35:40.000
Oh. Charlie.

437
00:35:41.160 --> 00:35:42.656
What brings you up here?

438
00:35:42.680 --> 00:35:44.216
I'd like to say it was social

439
00:35:44.240 --> 00:35:46.416
but I need to talk
to some of your team. Ah.

440
00:35:46.440 --> 00:35:49.056
Well. we're on a bit of a surge here
with the trade talks.

441
00:35:49.080 --> 00:35:50.520
Internal security. Barbara.

442
00:35:51.920 --> 00:35:54.176
So. who do you want to talk to?

443
00:35:54.200 --> 00:35:57.456
Anyone who's had cause to go to
Malware in the last two years or so.

444
00:35:57.480 --> 00:36:00.440
Right.
In that case. most of the team.

445
00:36:02.200 --> 00:36:04.040
I was hoping you weren't
going to say that. Mm.

446
00:36:05.480 --> 00:36:06.936
I'll get Calvin to bring
you the log.

447
00:36:06.960 --> 00:36:09.760
You can have the small
conference room. All right.

448
00:36:30.240 --> 00:36:31.456
Ah.

449
00:36:31.480 --> 00:36:32.976
What happened to you yesterday?

450
00:36:33.000 --> 00:36:35.376
Were you with Checkpoint Charlie
all that time?

451
00:36:35.400 --> 00:36:36.776
Mm.

452
00:36:36.800 --> 00:36:39.080
Did he find out you've been cheating
the fantasy football?

453
00:36:40.240 --> 00:36:42.256
{\an8}Using an algorithm is not cheating.

454
00:36:42.280 --> 00:36:43.720
{\an8}I think it probably is.

455
00:36:45.840 --> 00:36:47.320
What? I'm just saying.

456
00:36:49.000 --> 00:36:50.456
Did I miss something yesterday?

457
00:36:50.480 --> 00:36:51.656
No.

458
00:36:51.680 --> 00:36:53.336
So what's the big deal?

459
00:36:53.360 --> 00:36:54.896
There's no big deal.

460
00:36:54.920 --> 00:36:59.336
Just. as your line manager
in our non-hierarchical hierarchy.

461
00:36:59.360 --> 00:37:00.536
I'm looking out for you.

462
00:37:00.560 --> 00:37:02.000
Just checking in.

463
00:37:03.320 --> 00:37:04.840
Consider yourself checked in.

464
00:37:06.280 --> 00:37:07.616
ALL IN OFFICE GROAN

465
00:37:07.640 --> 00:37:08.856
Wait. was that you?

466
00:37:08.880 --> 00:37:10.000
I didn't do anything.

467
00:37:13.920 --> 00:37:17.296
The back door into the FSB system
Trusov left us.

468
00:37:17.320 --> 00:37:18.896
they've closed it.

469
00:37:18.920 --> 00:37:19.920
Fuck.

470
00:37:20.920 --> 00:37:23.576
Which means... Which means
they know we've been in there.

471
00:37:23.600 --> 00:37:26.800
and they won't be long in figuring
out how we got in. Oh. shit.

472
00:37:28.720 --> 00:37:29.720
We'd better tell Danny.

473
00:37:30.840 --> 00:37:32.200
Well. you'd better tell Danny.

474
00:37:33.640 --> 00:37:35.360
You know. line manager and all that.

475
00:37:43.200 --> 00:37:45.640
PHONE BEEPS

476
00:37:49.720 --> 00:37:51.696
Hello? Saara. where are you?

477
00:37:51.720 --> 00:37:54.416
Heading home.
You need to get a message to Vadim.

478
00:37:54.440 --> 00:37:55.896
The FSB know.

479
00:37:55.920 --> 00:37:57.136
Shit. How?

480
00:37:57.160 --> 00:37:59.216
We don't know. We just know they
closed the door on us.

481
00:37:59.240 --> 00:38:01.856
How did he get you
the first link to the FSB?

482
00:38:01.880 --> 00:38:03.016
Text message to my phone.

483
00:38:03.040 --> 00:38:04.736
All right. well they might
know about that as well.

484
00:38:04.760 --> 00:38:06.136
Just get a message to him.

485
00:38:06.160 --> 00:38:08.296
Tell him to get out of
wherever he is and go off-grid.

486
00:38:08.320 --> 00:38:10.776
The Russians know what he did.
his life is in danger.

487
00:38:10.800 --> 00:38:13.160
And you might want to do something
about your phone as well.

488
00:38:17.680 --> 00:38:18.680
Fuck.

489
00:39:32.360 --> 00:39:34.800
BEEP

490
00:39:38.280 --> 00:39:39.416
Where are you going?

491
00:39:39.440 --> 00:39:41.680
If you don't let me go.
they'll kill me.

492
00:39:46.520 --> 00:39:48.616
Put it on - anti-facial recognition.

493
00:39:48.640 --> 00:39:50.496
Make sure the design
faces the front.

494
00:39:50.520 --> 00:39:52.216
It pixelates the face.

495
00:39:52.240 --> 00:39:54.736
State Security are on their way.
the FSB are with them.

496
00:39:54.760 --> 00:39:56.896
But the FSB know what I've done.
They'll kill me.

497
00:39:56.920 --> 00:39:58.256
I've been monitoring you.

498
00:39:58.280 --> 00:40:00.840
Only I know you have been in contact
with someone on the outside.

499
00:40:02.240 --> 00:40:03.976
I am part of the democracy movement.

500
00:40:04.000 --> 00:40:07.216
I love my country.
but my country is not the CCP.

501
00:40:07.240 --> 00:40:09.800
I think you feel similarly about
your country and leadership.

502
00:40:11.600 --> 00:40:13.496
I've disconnected
the facial recognition. CCTV

503
00:40:13.520 --> 00:40:15.296
and alarms in the service elevator.

504
00:40:15.320 --> 00:40:17.336
You have three minutes
to get to the basement and out.

505
00:40:17.360 --> 00:40:18.976
This is the address of
a friend in the movement.

506
00:40:19.000 --> 00:40:20.656
Her name is Hai.
Maybe she can help.

507
00:40:20.680 --> 00:40:21.856
Go!

508
00:40:21.880 --> 00:40:23.080
Thank you.

509
00:40:40.520 --> 00:40:43.960
ALARM BLARES

510
00:40:47.760 --> 00:40:50.440
GATE BEEPS

511
00:41:13.360 --> 00:41:15.376
KNOCKING

512
00:41:15.400 --> 00:41:18.000
Barbara. Thanks for waiting.

513
00:41:19.480 --> 00:41:21.376
Well. I was here anyway -

514
00:41:21.400 --> 00:41:23.560
China trade talks. riveting.

515
00:41:25.120 --> 00:41:26.360
So...

516
00:41:27.520 --> 00:41:29.240
have you discovered
anything interesting?

517
00:41:30.440 --> 00:41:33.456
Only what a large department
you've become.

518
00:41:33.480 --> 00:41:35.040
Well. that's China for you.

519
00:41:36.480 --> 00:41:38.136
Mm.

520
00:41:38.160 --> 00:41:40.560
I had to go down to the cages
to get your file.

521
00:41:42.200 --> 00:41:45.256
My old MI6 file.
CHARLIE CHUCKLES

522
00:41:45.280 --> 00:41:47.720
I have my notes from
your vetting interview here.

523
00:41:49.080 --> 00:41:50.280
2015.

524
00:41:52.000 --> 00:41:54.056
Well. there's nothing like going
through your whole love life

525
00:41:54.080 --> 00:41:55.360
with your husband's best friend.

526
00:41:59.280 --> 00:42:00.360
We should begin.

527
00:42:01.920 --> 00:42:03.296
I understand you've found a way

528
00:42:03.320 --> 00:42:06.536
to launch our cyber offensive.
Lieutenant Colonel. Yes. sir.

529
00:42:06.560 --> 00:42:08.096
GCHQ reverse engineers

530
00:42:08.120 --> 00:42:10.656
showed great ingenuity
in re-establishing the comms.

531
00:42:10.680 --> 00:42:12.056
I'm glad to hear it.

532
00:42:12.080 --> 00:42:15.216
See? Making a difference already.

533
00:42:15.240 --> 00:42:16.520
We await orders.

534
00:42:17.720 --> 00:42:21.376
One last time. Foreign Secretary.
I strongly urge you to reconsider.

535
00:42:21.400 --> 00:42:24.096
Launching a cyber-attack
against Russia could be seen

536
00:42:24.120 --> 00:42:25.336
as a declaration of war.

537
00:42:25.360 --> 00:42:29.016
Lieutenant Colonel Cavendish.
the back door to the FSB has closed.

538
00:42:29.040 --> 00:42:31.520
Deploy our response to
Russia's attack.

539
00:42:32.680 --> 00:42:35.976
Now. if you'll excuse me.

540
00:42:36.000 --> 00:42:39.696
I am entertaining the German
ambassador at the Royal Opera.

541
00:42:39.720 --> 00:42:41.800
Die Walkure. Yes. sir.

542
00:43:05.200 --> 00:43:07.336
Orders to deploy degrading effects.

543
00:43:07.360 --> 00:43:08.936
Launch our cyber offensive.

544
00:43:08.960 --> 00:43:10.576
You found the way back in -

545
00:43:10.600 --> 00:43:12.016
would you like to do the honours?

546
00:43:12.040 --> 00:43:13.336
Pleasure.

547
00:43:13.360 --> 00:43:15.280
Bastards have caused us
enough trouble.

548
00:43:17.480 --> 00:43:20.600
Command Control E. HE TYPES.

549
00:43:21.600 --> 00:43:23.080
Boom!

550
00:43:37.920 --> 00:43:40.936
So. no material change there either?

551
00:43:40.960 --> 00:43:44.640
No. just a boring.
suburban mum's existence.

552
00:43:46.400 --> 00:43:47.960
You've never been boring. Barbara.

553
00:43:49.840 --> 00:43:51.736
You're too kind. Charlie.

554
00:43:51.760 --> 00:43:53.680
You've always been too kind.

555
00:43:54.840 --> 00:43:56.816
No. No big windfalls.

556
00:43:56.840 --> 00:43:59.496
no tall. dark strangers
taking me aside.

557
00:43:59.520 --> 00:44:01.456
Nothing much. in fact.

558
00:44:01.480 --> 00:44:03.936
The Malware department -

559
00:44:03.960 --> 00:44:07.696
you said you sometimes have
call to go there.

560
00:44:07.720 --> 00:44:10.016
Yeah. Most of us do.

561
00:44:10.040 --> 00:44:13.576
Yet at no point are you signed in
to the sandbox computer.

562
00:44:13.600 --> 00:44:15.976
I'm not sure

563
00:44:16.000 --> 00:44:17.360
I'd even have the clearance.

564
00:44:18.480 --> 00:44:20.096
But I've never needed to.

565
00:44:20.120 --> 00:44:23.096
I'm sure you've heard from others.

566
00:44:23.120 --> 00:44:27.736
the reverse engineer finds
a bit of Mandarin or Cantonese text.

567
00:44:27.760 --> 00:44:30.696
whoever answers the call
in my department sits with them

568
00:44:30.720 --> 00:44:33.656
as they walk us through it.
and we translate it on the hoof.

569
00:44:33.680 --> 00:44:34.920
Do you answer the call often?

570
00:44:36.600 --> 00:44:37.896
Not so much.

571
00:44:37.920 --> 00:44:41.696
I'm less across contemporary
and technical hacker slang

572
00:44:41.720 --> 00:44:43.240
than my younger colleagues.

573
00:44:44.320 --> 00:44:46.656
KNOCKING

574
00:44:46.680 --> 00:44:48.400
Boss. You need to see this.

575
00:44:49.440 --> 00:44:51.000
Give me a moment. Of course.

576
00:44:53.720 --> 00:44:55.816
Barbara. sorry.
I've kept you long enough.

577
00:44:55.840 --> 00:44:57.216
Oh. we're done?

578
00:44:57.240 --> 00:44:58.976
Yep. and you need to pick up
the boys.

579
00:44:59.000 --> 00:45:01.176
No. Anne picked them up.
they're at yours.

580
00:45:01.200 --> 00:45:03.640
Thank you.
and sorry for keeping you again.

581
00:45:04.920 --> 00:45:07.800
I think we've got him. but we need to
double and triple-check this.

582
00:45:19.360 --> 00:45:21.760
And it's definitely linked
to Phil Draper? Aye.

583
00:45:24.680 --> 00:45:26.216
Sorry.

584
00:45:26.240 --> 00:45:28.080
I forgot my smart card.

585
00:45:32.120 --> 00:45:35.296
TV: and Chinese money.
with access to the London markets.

586
00:45:35.320 --> 00:45:37.296
Is that correct. Mr Marston?

587
00:45:37.320 --> 00:45:39.456
The Prime Minister is working
around the clock... Hello?

588
00:45:39.480 --> 00:45:41.216
On this trade deal with China.

589
00:45:41.240 --> 00:45:42.736
Finance will be at its centre...

590
00:45:42.760 --> 00:45:44.216
Where is everybody?

591
00:45:44.240 --> 00:45:47.296
Fabian's asleep.
Mum's upstairs too.

592
00:45:47.320 --> 00:45:51.616
Finance. technology. manufacturing
and. of course. security.

593
00:45:51.640 --> 00:45:53.016
This trade deal with China...

594
00:45:53.040 --> 00:45:54.160
WHISPERS: Trust you?

595
00:45:55.400 --> 00:45:56.456
How can I trust you?

596
00:45:56.480 --> 00:45:58.760
PHONE RINGS

597
00:46:06.160 --> 00:46:07.496
David.

598
00:46:07.520 --> 00:46:09.296
I'm sorry to interrupt you at home

599
00:46:09.320 --> 00:46:12.080
but I thought you should know
first off...

600
00:46:13.680 --> 00:46:14.880
Charlie's found the mole.

601
00:46:17.440 --> 00:46:19.400
IN MANDARIN:

602
00:46:30.760 --> 00:46:33.160
Subtitles by Red Bee Media
